" /></a><br /> 那個...該不會真哪一天，主站會把 R.I.P.（安息吧！）這幾個字，掛在旁邊的哭臉面前？千萬不要啊！詳情聽說！<br /> <br /> 日前 Motorola 發佈的一則聲明稿，當中確實提及了為了維護廣大投資人，以及公司獲利層面的考量，將手機/行動裝置事業部切出 Motorola 旗下，成為一家獨立的公司，是一個相當有可能的選項。<br /> <br /> 至於將來可能切出的手機事業部將會有怎樣的發展，目前仍待董事會的進一步商議，甚至會以怎樣的面貌出現，目前咱們也不清楚，只能說，加油吧！MOTO！<br />  <br /> [Thanks Stasys; 出自 <a href="http://www.unwiredview.com/2008/01/31/motorola-is-dumping-mobile-phone-division/" linkindex="14">Unwired View</a>]<br /> <br /> [<a href="http://www.engadget.com/2008/01/31/motorola-officially-considering-dropping-its-phone-unit/">原文連結</a>]<br /><h6 style="clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;"></h6><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td style="text-align: left; vertical-align: top; padding: 2px; margin: 0; font-size: x-small;"></td><td style="text-align: right; vertical-align: top; padding: 2px; margin: 0; font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://chinese.engadget.com/2008/02/02/motorola-officially-considering-dropping-its-phone-unit/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent link to this entry">永久連結</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="http://chinese.engadget.com/forward/1103818/" title="Send this entry to a friend via email">轉寄</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="http://chinese.engadget.com/2008/02/02/motorola-officially-considering-dropping-its-phone-unit/#comments" title="View reader comments on this entry">發表回應</a></td></tr></table>]]></description><category>分割</category><category>MOTO</category><category>手機事業</category><dc:creator>Casper Kao</dc:creator><dc:date>2008-02-02T04:00:00+00:00</dc:date></item><item><title>現場瞻仰一下Sigma APO 200-500 F2.8巨炮風采</title><link>http://chinese.engadget.com/2008/02/02/sigma-apo-200-500-f2-8/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">http://chinese.engadget.com/2008/02/02/sigma-apo-200-500-f2-8/</guid><comments>http://chinese.engadget.com/2008/02/02/sigma-apo-200-500-f2-8/#comments</comments><description><![CDATA[<p>Filed under: <a href="http://chinese.engadget.com/category/digitalcameras/" rel="tag">數位相機</a></p><p><img alt="" src="http://www.engadget.com/media/2008/02/2008-02-01sigma-5-sm.jpg" /></p>
